snippet.title: [Arcade High Score] Snake Pit - 796,650 (1cc)
snippet.description:
Personal best high score, played as part of a CAGDC community challenge in 2009.

Snake Pit is a neat game from Bally Sente.

Controls include a trackball for movement and joystick for aiming the whip.
Additionally, after clearing Wave 14, you receive an item that allows you to push a button for around 7 seconds of invincibility, once per stage.

The settings are fairly generous with extra lives every 10,000 points, but it's still very possible to get stuck on some of the tougher stages.
